WEBVTT

00:04.787 --> 00:06.267
- Previously on
"The Arrangement"...

00:06.310 --> 00:07.572
- Thank you to everyone
who came out

00:07.616 --> 00:10.575
for the start of
"Technicolor Highway."

00:10.619 --> 00:12.055
You've never
carried a film before.

00:12.099 --> 00:14.318
- You are projecting your fear
onto me.

00:14.362 --> 00:16.494
You're scared shitless
that you're gonna mess this up.

00:16.538 --> 00:18.279
- I have Adam from the studio.

00:18.322 --> 00:19.497
- Tell him we just wrapped
and I'll get back to him...

00:19.541 --> 00:21.021
- He says it's important.

00:21.064 --> 00:22.326
The "Kill Plan" test numbers
just came in.

00:22.370 --> 00:23.675
- I'm just a stand-in
for the person

00:23.719 --> 00:25.373
who abandoned you.

00:25.416 --> 00:27.114
- You're talking about
my father?

00:27.157 --> 00:29.159
What's this?

00:29.203 --> 00:30.769
- He lives in Lompoc.

00:30.813 --> 00:32.683
- Kyle West is a product

00:32.728 --> 00:34.817
of the Institute
of the Higher Mind,

00:34.860 --> 00:38.081
which I've also heard
terrible stories about.

00:38.125 --> 00:40.083
- Hope's the one
who gave your naked pictures

00:40.127 --> 00:41.302
to the press.

00:41.345 --> 00:43.173
- We would make
amazing parents.

00:43.217 --> 00:45.523
And maybe it's time
to reopen that conversation.

00:45.567 --> 00:47.612
- I would have loved
to have you in my bed

00:47.656 --> 00:49.484
when Wes was in rehab.

00:49.527 --> 00:52.530
So we could have talked
about my failings as a mother.

00:52.574 --> 00:54.663
- Oh, hi, Wes,
I'm a friend of your mom's.

00:54.706 --> 00:55.794
I've been trying
to get a hold of her.

00:55.838 --> 00:58.188
Is she...?

00:58.232 --> 00:59.450
What?

01:01.409 --> 01:04.715
- "Access Hollywood" live
at the "Kill Plan" premiere.

01:04.760 --> 01:07.806
[cheers and applause]

01:07.850 --> 01:10.809
[lively pop music]

01:10.853 --> 01:15.075
♪

01:15.118 --> 01:17.120
Okay,
Kyle West and Megan Morrison

01:17.164 --> 01:19.383
should be arriving
any second.

01:19.427 --> 01:21.690
[crowd cheering]

01:22.691 --> 01:24.388
- Kyle?

01:24.432 --> 01:25.868
- Hmm?

01:25.911 --> 01:28.262
Hey.
How you feeling?

01:28.305 --> 01:30.481
- Me?
How are you feeling?

01:30.525 --> 01:31.743
- Fine.

01:31.787 --> 01:33.397
Yeah,
it's all part of the game.

01:33.441 --> 01:34.529
Sometimes you gotta lie
through your teeth.

01:34.572 --> 01:36.096
- Yeah, it's called "selling."

01:36.139 --> 01:37.836
Focus on the positives.
There are a few.

01:37.880 --> 01:39.403
- Yeah,
you get a chance to act.

01:39.447 --> 01:41.492
- No one does it better.

01:45.888 --> 01:47.150
[door opens]

01:47.194 --> 01:50.153
[cheers and applause]

01:50.197 --> 01:57.160
♪

01:57.204 --> 02:00.250
[indistinct shouting]

02:02.209 --> 02:04.428
- Can I have your autograph?

02:04.472 --> 02:07.431
[all cheering]

02:07.475 --> 02:13.263
♪

02:13.307 --> 02:16.440
- Here he is,
"Kill Plan" star Kyle West,

02:16.484 --> 02:18.225
my favorite actor.

02:18.268 --> 02:19.487
- Oh, Aubrey, enough's enough.

02:19.530 --> 02:21.141
You say that to everybody.

02:21.184 --> 02:22.316
You can't keep playing
with my heart like this.

02:22.359 --> 02:23.839
- [laughs]
Okay.

02:23.882 --> 02:26.494
"Kill Plan."
Tell us about this movie.

02:26.537 --> 02:28.626
- Ah, I am so excited
about this movie.

02:28.670 --> 02:30.150
You know,
I made it for the fans.

02:30.193 --> 02:31.455
And tonight,
the fans get to see it.

02:31.499 --> 02:33.414
So... that's what
it's all about, right?

02:33.457 --> 02:34.719
- You bet.
- Mm.

02:34.763 --> 02:36.417
- You look great tonight.
- So do you.

02:36.460 --> 02:37.635
- Thank you.
- Good to see you.

02:37.679 --> 02:39.333
- Nice to see you.
- [chuckles]

02:39.376 --> 02:42.336
[crowd cheering]

02:42.379 --> 02:49.473
♪

02:55.697 --> 02:58.743
[distant applause]

03:03.835 --> 03:06.708
- I liked it.

03:06.751 --> 03:09.580
The interrogation scenes
were riveting.

03:09.624 --> 03:10.886
- Yeah.
[sighs]

03:10.929 --> 03:13.280
You still... still pissed
you weren't in it?

03:13.323 --> 03:14.716
- [scoffs]

03:14.759 --> 03:16.805
Look,
the chemistry isn't killer,

03:16.848 --> 03:18.850
but you are.

03:18.894 --> 03:20.852
And that's what people go
to the movies for, right,

03:20.896 --> 03:23.464
a little Kyle West escape?

03:25.901 --> 03:27.555
- Can't argue with that.

03:27.598 --> 03:28.904
Escape.

03:28.947 --> 03:30.558
[sighs]

03:31.646 --> 03:33.343
Where's DeAnn?

03:33.387 --> 03:34.997
- I don't know.
Bathroom?

03:35.040 --> 03:37.347
- I'll go find her.

03:38.348 --> 03:40.437
- Is DeAnn okay?
She seems a bit off tonight.

03:40.481 --> 03:42.396
- Eh, she has a lot
on her mind.

03:42.439 --> 03:43.875
- About "Technicolor Highway"
or this?

03:43.919 --> 03:45.790
- Everything.
Look, I'm not gonna lie to you.

03:45.834 --> 03:49.316
Those testing numbers
caught me off-guard, too.

03:49.359 --> 03:50.839
How you doing, really?

03:50.882 --> 03:52.275
- [sighs]

03:52.319 --> 03:54.538
Directing.
It's the best kind of therapy.

03:54.582 --> 03:56.453
- But this is...
This is a new territory.

03:56.497 --> 03:57.759
You've never had a film
lose money before.

03:57.802 --> 03:58.890
- The movie hasn't even
opened yet.

03:58.934 --> 04:00.370
- I know.
I know.

04:00.414 --> 04:01.719
I'm just saying
we should prepare.

04:01.763 --> 04:03.808
Maybe do a couple
of morning sessions.

04:03.852 --> 04:05.941
I'll go as early as you want.

04:08.900 --> 04:11.947
- [crying]

04:12.991 --> 04:14.558
- Hey.

04:14.602 --> 04:17.474
Been looking everywhere
for you.

04:17.517 --> 04:19.302
- [sniffles]

04:19.346 --> 04:21.957
- All right, I didn't think
the movie was that bad.

04:22.000 --> 04:24.568
- [laughs]

04:24.612 --> 04:26.266
[sniffles]

04:26.309 --> 04:29.747
I'm sorry, I just...

04:29.791 --> 04:31.575
[sniffles]
I lost somebody

04:31.619 --> 04:34.752
that I was close to recently.

04:34.796 --> 04:37.625
Somebody that I went
to college with.

04:38.669 --> 04:40.802
- I'm so sorry.

04:41.455 --> 04:43.413
- So, um...

04:43.457 --> 04:46.895
all this tonight, it's hard.

04:47.809 --> 04:50.028
- Puts things in perspective,
huh?

04:54.598 --> 04:56.644
- Thanks.
- Of course.

05:01.605 --> 05:04.565
[tense music]

05:04.608 --> 05:08.003
♪

05:08.046 --> 05:10.005
- [laughs]

05:10.048 --> 05:14.836
♪

05:17.491 --> 05:20.450
I think you should do Fallon
while he's in I.A.

05:20.494 --> 05:21.625
Obviously because...

05:21.669 --> 05:23.366
- It's Fallon.
Yeah, good.

05:23.410 --> 05:25.368
- Other than that,
I think we should cut and run.

05:25.412 --> 05:26.543
As much as we can.

05:26.587 --> 05:28.371
- I want to do everything.

05:28.415 --> 05:30.634
I know the tracking
for "The Kill Plan" is bad.

05:30.678 --> 05:32.636
But if we promote this thing
the right way,

05:32.680 --> 05:34.072
I think we can salvage it.

05:34.116 --> 05:36.858
- Kyle, the early critical
response has...

05:36.901 --> 05:38.512
- Screw the critics.

05:38.555 --> 05:40.601
I made this movie
for the fans.

05:40.644 --> 05:43.125
It's... it's an escape.

05:43.168 --> 05:45.345
- Your focus needs to be
on directing.

05:45.388 --> 05:47.608
- And I'm gonna go straight
to set when we land.

05:47.651 --> 05:49.087
I'll make it all work.

05:49.131 --> 05:50.480
I'm gonna promote the hell
out of this thing,

05:50.524 --> 05:52.700
maybe recut the trailer.

05:52.743 --> 05:54.876
Look, all we need is
a good opening weekend.

05:56.000 --> 06:02.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

06:07.410 --> 06:08.890
- I was wrong.

06:09.717 --> 06:10.935
- Wrong about...?

06:10.979 --> 06:13.460
- You should have been
in this role.

06:13.503 --> 06:16.898
Amelia Briggs doesn't hold
a candle to you.

06:16.941 --> 06:18.856
- Yeah, well...

06:18.900 --> 06:20.031
what's done is done.

06:20.075 --> 06:22.817
And you can't change the past.

06:24.471 --> 06:26.603
- We can change
how it affects us.

06:28.083 --> 06:30.999
Have you reached out
to your father?

06:31.042 --> 06:33.523
♪

06:33.567 --> 06:35.438
- No.

06:35.482 --> 06:37.092
No, I haven't had a chance...

06:37.135 --> 06:39.181
- You're busy, I know,
but is that more important

06:39.224 --> 06:40.530
than healing?

06:40.574 --> 06:42.532
Megan, we course-corrected.

06:42.576 --> 06:45.100
You've got a clear path.

06:45.143 --> 06:47.102
Follow it.

06:47.145 --> 06:54.414
♪

07:09.777 --> 07:12.867
- Well, I guess I'm gonna have
to catch up with her.

07:12.910 --> 07:16.784
Kyle.
So... scene 34,

07:16.827 --> 07:19.090
Hooper and the motel clerk,
it's a bit of a gabfest.

07:19.134 --> 07:20.788
We need to gussy it up a bit.

07:20.831 --> 07:22.920
- That's why I got you, Mel.
To gussy.

07:22.964 --> 07:24.574
- Right, did you take a look
at the storyboards

07:24.618 --> 07:25.836
I sent you for scene 23?

07:25.880 --> 07:27.708
- Is that Kyle West?

07:27.751 --> 07:28.839
God!
[both laugh]

07:28.883 --> 07:30.667
- What's up?
- Hey, man.

07:30.711 --> 07:31.929
- You ready to stuff your face
with some wedding cake?

07:31.973 --> 07:33.627
- Yeah, Nasim texted me.

07:33.670 --> 07:34.932
You sure we're not imposing?

07:34.976 --> 07:36.107
- No, no, no.
It's Megan's idea.

07:36.151 --> 07:37.500
We need backup.
By the way,

07:37.544 --> 07:38.806
how you feeling
about the scene?

07:38.849 --> 07:39.937
- You mean,
how's Hooper feeling?

07:39.981 --> 07:41.504
We've merged into one person,

07:41.548 --> 07:43.637
and Hooper's got
some questions, man, so...

07:43.680 --> 07:45.769
- Interviews are all lined up
for crew lunch.

07:45.813 --> 07:47.467
- How many we got?
Eight?

07:47.510 --> 07:49.773
- 11.
Nine national, two local.

07:49.817 --> 07:51.209
And studio marketing's
on the phone.

07:51.253 --> 07:52.820
They want to talk
new trailer ideas.

07:52.863 --> 07:54.474
- And they're all good
with the turnaround?

07:54.517 --> 07:55.823
- Kyle, wait, before
we roll on this, can we...

07:55.866 --> 07:57.607
- We will discuss it, yeah.
Sit tight.

07:57.651 --> 07:58.913
- Kyle, storyboards?

07:58.956 --> 08:01.089
- Storyboards rock my world,
buddy.

08:01.132 --> 08:02.743
It's gonna be beautiful.

08:02.786 --> 08:04.962
♪

08:05.006 --> 08:06.921
- And it looks like
everything's been signed,

08:06.964 --> 08:08.792
so I put the waivers
on your desk.

08:08.836 --> 08:10.968
But just for the record,

08:11.012 --> 08:12.883
I'm not sure
how I feel about this.

08:12.927 --> 08:15.538
- Asking people to sign
a waiver before a seminar?

08:15.582 --> 08:17.192
I agree.
- No.

08:17.235 --> 08:21.283
Asking people to take off
their clothes during a seminar.

08:21.326 --> 08:22.545
- It's voluntary.

08:22.589 --> 08:24.808
- And maybe a bit gimmicky?

08:24.852 --> 08:27.289
- We're expanding, Shaun.
We've got to try new things.

08:27.332 --> 08:30.858
And... sometimes physical truth

08:30.901 --> 08:32.642
leads to emotional truth.

08:32.686 --> 08:34.078
That's what this is all about.

08:34.121 --> 08:35.515
- Hmm.

08:35.558 --> 08:38.256
- Do you have an issue
with your body?

08:38.299 --> 08:39.562
- No.

08:39.606 --> 08:40.736
- Then you should sign up.

08:40.780 --> 08:41.825
- [laughs]

08:41.869 --> 08:44.219
Wait.
You're joking, right?

08:44.261 --> 08:46.830
- No.
I welcome skeptics.

08:46.874 --> 08:48.571
And I value your opinion.

08:48.615 --> 08:49.833
If you still think
it's a gimmick,

08:49.877 --> 08:51.966
we'll kill the program.

08:55.360 --> 08:57.101
- Sorry to interrupt.

08:57.145 --> 08:59.756
- Oh, Megan Morrison, hey.

08:59.800 --> 09:00.844
[laughs]

09:00.888 --> 09:02.193
- [laughs politely]

09:02.237 --> 09:03.586
I could come back later if...

09:03.630 --> 09:05.022
- No, not at all.

09:05.066 --> 09:06.850
Staff meeting in five?

09:06.894 --> 09:08.939
- Mm-hmm.

09:10.767 --> 09:13.204
So...

09:13.248 --> 09:15.642
what's this crazy idea
you texted me about?

09:15.685 --> 09:16.817
I gotta go to this...

09:16.860 --> 09:19.036
- Staff meeting.
I know.

09:20.168 --> 09:23.563
I'm thinking
of reaching out to Hope.

09:23.606 --> 09:25.086
- No, you're not.

09:25.129 --> 09:28.089
- She has stories, Shaun.

09:28.132 --> 09:30.700
- She's not trustworthy.

09:30.744 --> 09:31.788
And you know it.

09:31.832 --> 09:34.225
- I know the risks, but...

09:34.269 --> 09:36.880
if she knows people
that have been

09:36.924 --> 09:38.752
through hell here, then...

09:38.795 --> 09:41.972
- Okay, we're working our asses
off to do this quietly,

09:42.016 --> 09:43.757
and you want to blab
to the one person

09:43.800 --> 09:46.324
who leaked your nude photos
all over the Internet...

09:46.368 --> 09:48.065
- No, I don't want to blab.

09:48.109 --> 09:50.372
I just want her to put me
in touch with some people.

09:50.415 --> 09:51.939
- [sighs]
- Look, we don't have

09:51.982 --> 09:53.244
anything else.

09:53.288 --> 09:55.203
We've flamed out
left and right.

09:55.246 --> 09:58.641
And Terence is in my head
more than ever.

09:58.685 --> 10:01.122
- In your head?
How?

10:01.165 --> 10:03.254
- He's just manipulative.

10:03.298 --> 10:07.650
Every day I have to feel it
and deal with it.

10:07.694 --> 10:09.304
I need a win.

10:09.347 --> 10:11.828
- I know.
And I get it.

10:11.872 --> 10:14.222
But we have to be patient
and smart.

10:14.265 --> 10:17.312
You want the whole thing
to blow up in our face?

10:19.706 --> 10:21.925
Let's find a time to meet up
later this week.

10:21.969 --> 10:24.754
We'll figure this out, okay?

10:24.798 --> 10:26.930
I gotta go.

10:26.974 --> 10:29.803
[indistinct chatter]

10:29.846 --> 10:36.940
♪

11:01.704 --> 11:03.271
[cell phone chimes]

11:13.150 --> 11:15.283
[solemn music playing]

11:15.326 --> 11:17.633
[indistinct chatter]

11:17.677 --> 11:24.684
♪

11:26.511 --> 11:30.124
- Excuse me.
Wes?

11:30.167 --> 11:31.691
I'm DeAnn Anderson.

11:31.734 --> 11:33.605
We spoke on the phone
last week.

11:33.649 --> 11:35.172
I'm a friend of your mom's
from...

11:35.216 --> 11:37.566
- College, yeah.
I remember.

11:37.609 --> 11:39.568
Um, thank you so much
for coming.

11:39.611 --> 11:42.614
Excuse me.
Thanks.

11:42.658 --> 11:44.747
Uh, we can...
- Oh.

11:44.791 --> 11:47.054
I'm so sorry, I didn't mean
to interrupt all of that.

11:47.097 --> 11:49.447
- Interrupt?
You saved me.

11:49.491 --> 11:51.232
If I have to thank
one more person

11:51.275 --> 11:53.451
for their kind words
and prayers...

11:53.495 --> 11:55.366
Jesus, I might kill myself.

11:55.410 --> 11:58.369
- Oh, you might not want
to say that at a funeral.

11:58.413 --> 11:59.544
- [chuckles]

11:59.588 --> 12:01.546
- Um...

12:01.590 --> 12:04.506
Wow, now I don't know if
I should say what I came over

12:04.549 --> 12:07.074
to you to say.
It's gonna sound so trite.

12:07.117 --> 12:09.729
- Go ahead.
Join the trite party.

12:12.340 --> 12:14.734
- Your mom was
a wonderful woman.

12:17.171 --> 12:19.129
She meant a lot to me.

12:19.173 --> 12:21.218
And...

12:22.437 --> 12:24.787
More than I can say,
really, right now.

12:24.831 --> 12:28.138
So... that's all.

12:28.182 --> 12:30.575
And you have all of my prayers.
[laughs]

12:30.619 --> 12:31.751
- [laughs]

12:31.794 --> 12:34.057
- [sniffles]

12:36.407 --> 12:38.496
- You meant a lot to her.

12:39.671 --> 12:41.630
- She talked about me?

12:41.673 --> 12:43.066
To you?

12:43.110 --> 12:45.068
- Not much.

12:45.112 --> 12:48.071
She kept a picture of you
on our living room mantle.

12:48.115 --> 12:51.727
She didn't have many photos
of people lying around.

12:51.771 --> 12:55.165
- She talked about you a lot.

12:55.209 --> 12:56.732
- Yeah.

12:56.776 --> 13:00.040
About what a screw-up I am.

13:00.083 --> 13:04.392
How all I ever did was
cause stress in her life.

13:04.435 --> 13:07.351
Wish I could've just
figured my shit out

13:07.395 --> 13:10.790
on my own and...

13:10.833 --> 13:13.140
I...
[sighs]

13:14.794 --> 13:17.709
I'm sorry, I'm rambling.
I... I...

13:17.753 --> 13:21.409
- It's okay.
It's okay.

13:21.452 --> 13:23.759
- [sighs]

13:23.803 --> 13:26.240
- So, what's next?

13:26.283 --> 13:27.676
- I don't know.

13:27.719 --> 13:29.591
I might stay at her place
here in Napa,

13:29.634 --> 13:33.073
but that's kind of depressing.

13:33.116 --> 13:36.206
"Movie producer."

13:36.250 --> 13:38.469
That's right,
you work with Kyle West.

13:38.513 --> 13:40.471
- I do.

13:40.515 --> 13:43.474
Wes... I'm here.

13:43.518 --> 13:46.608
If you need anything, please.

13:46.651 --> 13:49.437
My door's always open.

13:49.480 --> 13:52.440
[solemn music]

13:52.483 --> 13:55.443
♪

14:02.667 --> 14:04.626
- Megan Morrison.

14:04.669 --> 14:06.584
- Hey, Hope.

14:06.628 --> 14:08.151
You look great.

14:08.195 --> 14:10.284
- Thanks.

14:13.678 --> 14:14.810
- I appreciate you coming.

14:14.854 --> 14:16.551
- Yeah.

14:16.594 --> 14:20.207
Whoever said hiking is fun
is a big, dirty liar.

14:20.250 --> 14:21.556
My glutes are burning.

14:21.599 --> 14:23.863
So, that's good.

14:23.906 --> 14:25.255
'Cause I'm an action heroine
now,

14:25.299 --> 14:26.822
so gotta keep that shit tight.

14:26.866 --> 14:28.650
- I saw.
Congratulations.

14:28.693 --> 14:30.391
The show looks badass.

14:30.434 --> 14:33.785
- Yeah, I get to kill
and have sex with aliens.

14:33.829 --> 14:35.875
So... it's my dream job.

14:35.918 --> 14:37.311
- [laughs]

14:37.354 --> 14:39.182
- Yeah.

14:40.227 --> 14:43.534
And you, engaged.

14:43.578 --> 14:45.667
Read all about it.

14:49.366 --> 14:51.760
- Look, Hope,

14:51.803 --> 14:53.631
the reason I asked you
to meet me...

14:53.675 --> 14:56.721
- Yeah,
your texts were mad ambiguous.

14:56.765 --> 14:58.941
- I remember you saying
that you knew people

14:58.985 --> 15:01.901
who had bad experiences

15:01.944 --> 15:03.903
with the Institute,

15:03.946 --> 15:06.209
and I need to talk to them.

15:07.732 --> 15:09.343
- Why?

15:10.910 --> 15:12.346
- I can't tell you.

15:12.389 --> 15:14.348
It's... sensitive.

15:14.391 --> 15:15.697
- Uh, okay, well,
are you, like,

15:15.740 --> 15:17.786
an IHM assassin now
or something?

15:17.829 --> 15:19.657
- No.
No, I...

15:19.701 --> 15:21.355
- 'Cause I don't want the
Institute's minions after me.

15:21.398 --> 15:22.704
- All right, look, never mind.

15:22.747 --> 15:25.968
This was... a mistake.

15:26.012 --> 15:28.492
- Well, I just...

15:28.536 --> 15:30.755
No, okay, wait.
Wait, wait.

15:32.975 --> 15:34.934
I do have a friend,
an actor friend of mine.

15:34.977 --> 15:36.936
His boyfriend is IHM,

15:36.979 --> 15:40.417
and apparently he's seen
some pretty messed-up shit.

15:40.461 --> 15:42.550
So...

15:42.593 --> 15:44.682
he might be willing to talk.

15:47.424 --> 15:50.732
- Wow.
These really are beautiful.

15:50.775 --> 15:53.778
- Ah, now,
this one reminds me of you.

15:53.822 --> 15:55.737
- The tall white one?

15:55.780 --> 15:57.391
- Elegant, straightforward,

15:57.434 --> 15:58.740
not trying too hard.

15:58.783 --> 16:00.002
- Oh.

16:00.046 --> 16:01.569
I think we might be
over-thinking this.

16:01.612 --> 16:02.874
- Yeah.

16:02.918 --> 16:04.659
- Babe, put your phone away.

16:04.702 --> 16:07.401
- Kyle, you got to see this.

16:07.444 --> 16:09.490
[rock music playing]

16:09.533 --> 16:11.535
- When I read the script,

16:11.579 --> 16:12.797
I knew that "The Kill Plan"
was a movie that I had to do.

16:12.841 --> 16:14.364
It's fun.

16:14.408 --> 16:15.713
Sometimes
you just need an escape.

16:15.757 --> 16:17.280
An escape.
An e-e-e-e-escape

16:17.324 --> 16:18.455
[voice distorted]
An escape.

16:18.499 --> 16:20.588
It can be an es-ca-ca-ca-cape.

16:20.631 --> 16:21.850
[voice distorted]
Escape.

16:21.893 --> 16:23.417
It's fun.
A great escape.

16:23.460 --> 16:24.984
[dynamic music, explosion]

16:28.813 --> 16:31.338
- [laughs]

16:31.381 --> 16:32.948
- Congrats, man.
Hey.

16:32.992 --> 16:35.429
You got your own Ben Affleck
"Hello Darkness" video.

16:35.472 --> 16:36.908
There's a half-million views
already.

16:36.952 --> 16:38.606
- Hey, I've finally arrived.

16:38.649 --> 16:40.303
[all chuckle]

16:40.347 --> 16:42.305
Let them eat cake.

16:42.349 --> 16:45.308
[dark music]

16:45.352 --> 16:48.572
♪

16:48.616 --> 16:51.619
So, is strawberry cream
the winner?

16:52.750 --> 16:54.665
- It's a frontrunner, yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

16:54.709 --> 16:57.494
- If it fits with
the IHM color scheme.

16:57.538 --> 16:59.627
- Yeah,
we'll run it by everybody.

16:59.670 --> 17:00.758
- Hm.

17:03.805 --> 17:06.763
Are you sure you're okay?

17:06.808 --> 17:07.809
- With what?

17:07.852 --> 17:09.463
The cakes?

17:09.506 --> 17:10.986
- The video.

17:11.030 --> 17:13.075
- Ah, of course.

17:13.118 --> 17:14.903
Viral marketing.
Look, it's organic.

17:14.945 --> 17:16.383
It's the best kind.

17:16.425 --> 17:19.777
- Well, I would be
a little... embarrassed.

17:19.820 --> 17:22.867
- Yeah, well, you need
a thick skin in this business.

17:25.608 --> 17:28.002
- Kyle,
you don't have to do this.

17:28.047 --> 17:30.005
I saw another batch of reviews
came out.

17:30.049 --> 17:31.833
You must have seen them.

17:31.876 --> 17:32.877
And the buzz online is...

17:32.921 --> 17:34.879
- What are you doing?

17:34.923 --> 17:36.881
You want me to get upset?

17:36.925 --> 17:38.796
- Of course not.

17:38.840 --> 17:41.582
I just want you
to be real with me.

17:41.625 --> 17:43.453
We're getting married.

17:43.497 --> 17:45.020
And that means
supporting each other

17:45.064 --> 17:47.849
through the good, the bad,
and the ups and the downs and...

17:47.892 --> 17:49.677
- Megan.
- I mean it.

17:49.720 --> 17:52.027
Right, the world could be
falling down around us,

17:52.071 --> 17:54.377
and we need to be there
for each other.

17:54.421 --> 17:57.511
- Oh, Jesus, just stop.

17:57.554 --> 17:59.861
[sighs]
You and Terence.

17:59.904 --> 18:00.862
[sighs]

18:00.905 --> 18:02.124
- Me and Terence what?

18:02.168 --> 18:03.691
- You guys are both
acting like

18:03.734 --> 18:05.867
I should be bracing myself
for a crash.

18:05.910 --> 18:08.870
I'm just doing my job,
promoting my work.

18:08.913 --> 18:11.394
[solemn music]

18:11.438 --> 18:13.396
- Okay.

18:13.440 --> 18:16.530
♪

18:16.573 --> 18:18.140
- You do realize
that if we had kids,

18:18.184 --> 18:21.796
all of this,
fancy dinners...

18:21.839 --> 18:23.798
not happening for a long time?

18:23.841 --> 18:25.582
- Oh, please,
you know we'd hire help.

18:25.626 --> 18:26.888
- Oh, of course, because

18:26.931 --> 18:28.455
having children is
so much easier

18:28.498 --> 18:30.065
when you don't actually
have to parent them.

18:30.109 --> 18:31.675
- We'd be great parents.

18:31.719 --> 18:33.764
We'd be structured, focused,
affectionate.

18:33.808 --> 18:35.592
And our kid would be
a knockout,

18:35.636 --> 18:37.551
especially with your genes.

18:37.594 --> 18:39.683
- Okay, thank you.

18:39.727 --> 18:42.599
Terence, at our age,

18:42.643 --> 18:44.732
this is a big choice.

18:44.775 --> 18:46.821
And you haven't been yourself,
not for weeks.

18:46.864 --> 18:50.390
So, I need to know why.
Why do you want this?

18:50.433 --> 18:52.740
[romantic piano music playing]

18:52.783 --> 18:54.568
- I guess...

18:54.611 --> 18:56.570
I want to
leave something behind.

18:56.613 --> 18:58.137
A piece of myself.

18:58.180 --> 18:59.138
Life is fleeting.

18:59.181 --> 19:02.576
Time... is fleeting.

19:02.619 --> 19:06.580
And I have been thinking
about that a lot lately.

19:06.623 --> 19:09.104
Mortality.
Our mortality.

19:09.148 --> 19:11.541
And... us.

19:11.585 --> 19:13.761
Our relationship.

19:13.804 --> 19:15.197
- Our relationship is fine.

19:15.241 --> 19:16.677
- No, it's not fine,

19:16.720 --> 19:18.679
and I don't want it
to be just fine.

19:18.722 --> 19:19.810
We've been distant
for a while.

19:19.854 --> 19:20.985
You have.

19:21.029 --> 19:22.726
I love you, DeAnn.

19:22.770 --> 19:24.728
I don't say it enough.

19:24.772 --> 19:26.208
But you're... you're immersed
in your work.

19:26.252 --> 19:27.601
Me and mine.

19:27.644 --> 19:29.603
We pass each other by.

19:29.646 --> 19:32.867
And I don't want to die
with that memory of us.

19:34.260 --> 19:37.524
[both moaning]

19:41.876 --> 19:44.966
[moaning climaxes]

19:51.190 --> 19:53.148
- Where'd you just go?

19:59.894 --> 20:01.765
- Uh... hmm?

20:01.809 --> 20:03.811
- And cut.

20:03.854 --> 20:06.814
All right, we got it,
great work.

20:07.989 --> 20:10.209
- Call time's at 6:00 a.m.
tomorrow, thanks.

20:10.252 --> 20:11.645
[phone chimes]
Okay, that's a wrap!

20:11.688 --> 20:13.647
- Good job.
- Yeah.

20:13.690 --> 20:14.952
[cell phone chimes]

20:16.998 --> 20:18.217
[cell phone chimes]

20:19.653 --> 20:21.220
- Strong work, Megan.

20:21.263 --> 20:23.004
- Where you off to?

20:23.047 --> 20:26.312
- Yoga, then maybe drinks with
Shaun to offset the yoga.

20:27.878 --> 20:29.967
- Bye.
- Bye.

20:30.011 --> 20:32.100
- Zach, meet me at the trailer,
okay?

20:32.143 --> 20:34.624
I want to leave for Fallon
in five.

20:34.668 --> 20:36.147
You coming?
Jimmy loves you.

20:36.191 --> 20:37.758
- No, not this time.

20:37.801 --> 20:39.803
So, are you sure we got that?

20:39.847 --> 20:40.891
- Got what?

20:40.935 --> 20:42.153
- That last scene.

20:42.197 --> 20:43.677
Xavier felt flat.

20:43.720 --> 20:46.810
- Flat?
How closer were you watching?

20:46.854 --> 20:48.856
- Look, I think
he could have gone deeper.

20:48.899 --> 20:51.032
He's supposed to be thinking
about every bad thing

20:51.075 --> 20:53.034
he's ever done in his life,
and it played like

20:53.077 --> 20:56.255
he was trying to decide between
Thai food or Chinese.

20:56.298 --> 20:57.908
- That's harsh.

20:57.952 --> 21:00.171
We got it.
I felt good.

21:00.215 --> 21:02.304
- And you don't want
to be late for Fallon.

21:02.348 --> 21:04.132
- [sighs]
What's that mean?

21:04.175 --> 21:05.960
- It means you're distracted.

21:06.003 --> 21:07.788
And you have been ever since
the testing numbers came out.

21:07.831 --> 21:09.311
- Distracted?
- Yeah.

21:09.355 --> 21:12.140
When you're here,
you're not here.

21:12.183 --> 21:14.447
I know you, Kyle.
I can feel it.

21:14.490 --> 21:16.100
- I don't need this from you.

21:16.144 --> 21:18.102
- Okay, well,
you're gonna get it anyway.

21:18.146 --> 21:20.888
This movie
will not direct itself.

21:20.931 --> 21:23.238
Okay?

21:23.282 --> 21:26.110
Tell Jimmy I said hi.

21:39.123 --> 21:40.168
- Hey.

21:40.211 --> 21:42.475
- Hey.
Where is he?

21:42.518 --> 21:44.781
- He'll be here soon.

21:46.435 --> 21:48.872
- Still driving
the dream machine.

21:48.916 --> 21:50.352
Figured you might upgrade.

21:50.396 --> 21:52.920
- No, why?
Just because I got a show?

21:52.963 --> 21:55.879
Shit, roll with the friends
you came with.

21:55.923 --> 21:57.925
That's how I like to party.

21:59.100 --> 22:01.015
- By stripping
our physical barriers away,

22:01.058 --> 22:02.451
literally stripping,

22:02.495 --> 22:04.235
each of you can uncover
something real

22:04.279 --> 22:06.237
about yourselves.

22:06.281 --> 22:08.805
I know it's tougher for some.

22:08.849 --> 22:11.330
I can sense a few skeptics
in the room.

22:11.373 --> 22:13.506
But that's okay.

22:16.117 --> 22:18.380
That's why we're here.

22:18.424 --> 22:21.470
So, who wants to go first?

22:26.780 --> 22:29.739
[solemn music]

22:29.783 --> 22:36.877
♪

22:38.226 --> 22:40.184
- Does Kyle know you're here?

22:40.228 --> 22:43.057
- No.
Um...

22:43.100 --> 22:45.538
I'm currently having drinks
with Shaun.

22:45.581 --> 22:47.931
- Oh, fun.
- Yeah.

22:47.975 --> 22:50.934
- So, this is like a cold feet
thing you're having or...?

22:50.978 --> 22:53.023
- No.
I love Kyle.

22:53.067 --> 22:55.069
I'm marrying him.

22:55.112 --> 22:57.245
- You're marrying him.

22:57.288 --> 22:59.552
But I mean,
he is the face of the cult

22:59.595 --> 23:01.902
that you're trying
to get dirt on, right?

23:01.945 --> 23:04.295
- It's complicated.

23:06.254 --> 23:08.038
- It's gonna be amazing.

23:08.082 --> 23:09.300
- What?

23:09.344 --> 23:10.998
- The wedding.

23:11.041 --> 23:14.262
I read all about it
in "Us Weekly" magazine.

23:14.305 --> 23:17.483
- Yeah, well,
that wedding will be amazing.

23:17.526 --> 23:19.049
We'll see how
the real one turns out...

23:19.093 --> 23:20.877
[pounding]
- Oh!

23:20.921 --> 23:22.052
Holy shit!

23:22.096 --> 23:23.445
- Okay, whoa, whoa, whoa,
no, no...

23:23.489 --> 23:25.186
- Get back!
- I'll just... let me just...

23:25.229 --> 23:26.317
- Get the hell out of here!
- Hold on one second.

23:26.361 --> 23:28.450
Here, hey, have a good night.

23:28.494 --> 23:30.539
Bye.

23:30.583 --> 23:32.236
Lock the doors, though.

23:32.280 --> 23:34.369
- Sleep with a guy once...

23:34.413 --> 23:37.154
- [laughs]
- Never leaves you alone.

23:37.198 --> 23:38.329
[both laughing]

23:38.373 --> 23:39.983
- And so, I told Xavier,

23:40.027 --> 23:42.029
I've heard that song
8 million times,

23:42.072 --> 23:44.292
and I always knew we'd meet
at some point.

23:44.335 --> 23:47.164
And then
I screwed his brains out.

23:47.208 --> 23:50.037
- Does that make this easier?

23:50.080 --> 23:51.604
- What?
- Using innuendo

23:51.647 --> 23:53.910
to mask what's real.

23:56.522 --> 23:58.045
- Hey, look, I'm an actor,

23:58.088 --> 24:00.221
so this is all...

24:02.266 --> 24:04.486
I don't have a problem
with nudity.

24:04.530 --> 24:06.357
- You equate the two?

24:06.401 --> 24:09.012
- No.
[chuckles softly]

24:09.056 --> 24:10.492
I'm not following.

24:10.536 --> 24:13.016
- Acting, your profession.
And this.

24:13.060 --> 24:15.105
Nudity.
Your body.

24:16.455 --> 24:18.500
- I'm a physical person.

24:18.544 --> 24:21.503
Okay, I use my physicality
in my roles, in my work,

24:21.547 --> 24:24.027
and that's...

24:31.078 --> 24:34.864
I never used to get roles
in high school.

24:34.908 --> 24:39.173
And then in college,
I... blossomed.

24:39.216 --> 24:42.655
And then things got easier.

24:42.698 --> 24:46.659
[eerie music]

24:46.702 --> 24:48.051
- [laughing]
- That was not even

24:48.095 --> 24:49.662
the director.
He's literally the guy

24:49.705 --> 24:51.185
who plays my alien dad.

24:51.228 --> 24:52.969
- So, what, you're half-alien,
too?

24:53.013 --> 24:54.536
- Wow, Megan, that's offensive.

24:54.580 --> 24:55.929
- [laughs]
- Honestly...

24:55.972 --> 24:58.148
- That's great.
- [laughs]

24:59.585 --> 25:02.544
[tense music]

25:02.588 --> 25:07.549
♪

25:07.593 --> 25:10.117
- What the hell is that?

25:13.337 --> 25:16.558
You want to check on your guy,
see if he's close?

25:20.693 --> 25:21.650
Hope?

25:21.694 --> 25:23.217
- [sighs]

25:23.260 --> 25:24.261
I really don't want you
to get mad.

25:24.305 --> 25:26.176
But Thai texted me

25:26.220 --> 25:28.004
right before you showed up,

25:28.048 --> 25:31.573
and his boyfriend kind of
got nervous and backed out.

25:31.617 --> 25:32.574
- Classic.

25:32.618 --> 25:35.098
- Megan... come on.

25:35.142 --> 25:36.970
Megan.

25:37.013 --> 25:39.102
Come on.
I don't know Thai.

25:39.146 --> 25:41.017
I mean, I can reach out
to other people who...

25:41.061 --> 25:42.671
- No, don't.
You lied to me, Hope.

25:42.715 --> 25:44.281
I'm out.

25:44.325 --> 25:45.935
- Okay, I'm sorry.
I just knew that

25:45.979 --> 25:48.242
if I told you that,
then you would leave and...

25:48.285 --> 25:49.591
- You know, Shaun was right.

25:49.635 --> 25:51.288
I shouldn't have even bothered
with you.

25:51.332 --> 25:52.333
- I... listen...
- It's like the same thing...

25:52.376 --> 25:54.204
- I miss you.

25:54.248 --> 25:55.466
[solemn music]

25:55.510 --> 25:58.121
Getting a break,
being on a show,

25:58.165 --> 26:01.298
that's what
we always talked about, right?

26:01.342 --> 26:04.737
And then look at us.
We're finally here, and...

26:04.780 --> 26:08.610
it just feels shitty.

26:08.654 --> 26:11.482
Because I can't share it
with you.

26:11.526 --> 26:14.094
And I know,
I brought this on myself.

26:14.137 --> 26:15.748
- Stop, I-I knew
this was a mistake.

26:15.791 --> 26:19.055
I... I have to go.

26:19.099 --> 26:22.189
♪

26:26.585 --> 26:27.542
- How are you feeling
right now?

26:27.586 --> 26:29.675
- [gasps]

26:29.718 --> 26:34.114
Uh, my stomach is
doing summersaults.

26:34.157 --> 26:37.247
Trying hard to breathe, and
everyone is looking at me.

26:38.161 --> 26:40.120
- You're embarrassed.

26:40.163 --> 26:41.687
- [chuckles softly]

26:41.730 --> 26:44.341
I wish I wasn't.

26:44.385 --> 26:46.735
Didn't used to be.

26:48.258 --> 26:50.739
- Explore that.

26:50.783 --> 26:53.176
- Um... when I was a kid,

26:53.220 --> 26:56.527
I was naked all the time.

26:56.571 --> 26:58.225
You couldn't pay me
to wear clothes.

26:58.268 --> 27:00.357
[laughs]

27:02.838 --> 27:05.362
I remember that.
There was this...

27:05.406 --> 27:07.408
There was this picture
my mom took of me

27:07.451 --> 27:10.716
when I was, like, six.

27:10.759 --> 27:14.241
[laughs softly]
It was of me vacuuming naked.

27:14.284 --> 27:17.244
- Have you seen it recently?

27:17.287 --> 27:18.680
- Yeah.

27:18.724 --> 27:21.204
We pulled it out
a couple years ago,

27:21.248 --> 27:23.250
me and my mom.

27:23.293 --> 27:25.600
- Close your eyes.

27:25.644 --> 27:27.080
- [clears throat]

27:27.123 --> 27:29.604
- Take a deep breath.

27:29.648 --> 27:32.259
- [exhales]

27:33.913 --> 27:36.089
- Put yourself
back in that moment.

27:36.132 --> 27:37.743
A couple years ago.

27:37.786 --> 27:39.875
It's you and your mom.

27:41.442 --> 27:43.792
What did you feel
when you saw it?

27:47.883 --> 27:48.841
- Sad.

27:48.884 --> 27:50.451
- Why?

27:50.494 --> 27:51.800
Why?

27:51.844 --> 27:54.150
- [sighs]

27:55.848 --> 27:57.719
Because it was before...

27:57.763 --> 27:59.808
- Before what?

28:01.505 --> 28:04.465
- My parents divorce.

28:04.508 --> 28:07.468
They split up the next year.

28:08.948 --> 28:12.299
Everything was just...
different.

28:12.342 --> 28:14.388
- Why were you different?

28:16.346 --> 28:18.740
- I felt different.

28:20.220 --> 28:22.701
I was different.

28:22.744 --> 28:24.572
- Why were you different?

28:24.615 --> 28:27.575
[solemn music]

28:27.618 --> 28:30.447
- Because they made me choose.

28:30.491 --> 28:32.754
♪

28:32.798 --> 28:35.322
- [sighs]

28:35.365 --> 28:41.502
♪

28:41.545 --> 28:43.896
- I need to swap out this
dick sock... it's kind of itchy.

28:43.939 --> 28:46.463
- Yeah, you're not allowed
to say "dick sock," okay?

28:46.507 --> 28:48.335
Please, come on.
- Sorry.

28:48.378 --> 28:50.380
I won't say "dick sock"
anymore.

28:50.424 --> 28:53.383
[both laugh]

28:59.563 --> 29:01.261
- Wes?

29:01.304 --> 29:02.610
- Hi.
- Hi, welcome.

29:02.653 --> 29:04.177
- Thank you.

29:04.220 --> 29:06.527
So, this is where
the magic happens?

29:06.570 --> 29:10.400
- Yeah, yeah,
you can smell it in the air.

29:10.444 --> 29:12.794
Um... I'm really glad
you called.

29:12.838 --> 29:15.275
- Me too, and thank you so much
for the invite.

29:15.318 --> 29:17.407
I've never been
on a real set before.

29:17.451 --> 29:18.974
- Okay, well...

29:19.018 --> 29:21.803
we have a pretty
sensitive scene up now.

29:21.847 --> 29:24.458
So, Danny here is gonna
take you on a tour

29:24.501 --> 29:25.981
of the other stages,
and when we move on

29:26.025 --> 29:29.289
to the next scene, then
you can come back and watch.

29:29.332 --> 29:30.464
Sound good?
- Okay.

29:30.507 --> 29:31.552
- Okay, great.
- All right.

29:31.595 --> 29:32.945
- Thanks, Danny.

29:42.606 --> 29:45.392
[soft music]

29:45.435 --> 29:48.830
♪

29:48.874 --> 29:50.527
- We need her full leg
in frame,

29:50.571 --> 29:52.268
or it won't cut together.

29:52.312 --> 29:53.835
- Megan, do you mind lifting
your leg to the right?

29:53.879 --> 29:55.489
- [panting]

29:55.532 --> 29:56.707
- Hair more.

29:56.751 --> 29:58.666
- A hair more, Megan.

29:58.709 --> 30:00.581
That's perfect.

30:00.624 --> 30:03.279
- I'm sorry, where is my hand
supposed to be, again?

30:03.323 --> 30:05.847
- Left hand on the back.
Right hand on the ass.

30:09.459 --> 30:11.722
- Ah... ow, ow.

30:11.766 --> 30:12.854
You got my leg.

30:12.898 --> 30:13.855
- Cut!
[bell rings]

30:13.899 --> 30:16.510
- All right, that's a cut.

30:16.553 --> 30:18.033
- [sighs]

30:18.077 --> 30:19.469
What happened?

30:19.513 --> 30:20.993
- Just a leg cramp

30:21.036 --> 30:22.821
from being stuck
in that position for too long.

30:22.864 --> 30:24.431
Ow.
- Here?

30:24.474 --> 30:25.824
- Ow.
Yes.

30:25.867 --> 30:27.521
Ooh, thank you.

30:27.564 --> 30:29.392
Thanks.

30:29.436 --> 30:32.482
[indistinct chatter]

30:40.664 --> 30:42.318
- You were right
the other night.

30:42.362 --> 30:43.972
- About what?

30:44.016 --> 30:47.976
- The truth about
"The Kill Plan."

30:48.020 --> 30:50.674
Totally humiliating.

30:51.806 --> 30:52.851
- Sweetie.

30:52.894 --> 30:54.287
- Yeah.

30:54.330 --> 30:56.376
It's like... it's as if

30:56.419 --> 30:59.640
I have these voices
in my head...

30:59.683 --> 31:01.555
you know, screaming at me,

31:01.598 --> 31:04.079
reminding me: "Of course."

31:04.123 --> 31:05.951
"Of course it's bad.

31:05.994 --> 31:08.867
"Failing.
'Cause that's what you are.

31:08.910 --> 31:10.346
"A failure.

31:10.390 --> 31:12.348
"And now
everyone's gonna know it.

31:12.392 --> 31:14.481
The truth."

31:17.136 --> 31:20.052
You know what scares me
the most?

31:20.095 --> 31:22.924
Is the thought that...

31:22.968 --> 31:25.448
you'd think that.

31:26.710 --> 31:28.625
- I would never think that.

31:28.669 --> 31:30.366
Ever.

31:35.023 --> 31:37.852
But I do sort of love
hearing that

31:37.896 --> 31:42.552
somebody so talented
has those voices, too.

31:48.036 --> 31:49.864
- Okay, real talk.

31:49.908 --> 31:51.735
- Mm.
- This scene.

31:51.779 --> 31:54.608
Is it working for you?

31:54.651 --> 31:57.698
- I trust your vision, Kyle.

31:59.004 --> 32:01.049
Is it your vision?

32:04.618 --> 32:05.749
- Here.

32:05.793 --> 32:07.838
Ah.

32:07.882 --> 32:10.145
- We gonna reset?

32:10.189 --> 32:12.931
- Let's try
something different.

32:19.763 --> 32:21.722
Let it build.

32:21.765 --> 32:23.898
Whenever you're ready, move in.

32:23.942 --> 32:26.901
[poignant music]

32:26.945 --> 32:33.995
♪

32:42.090 --> 32:45.441
Hooper, remove her shirt.

32:45.485 --> 32:52.579
♪

32:56.496 --> 32:58.454
Take her in.

32:58.498 --> 33:02.197
♪

33:02.241 --> 33:04.199
Now let go.

33:04.243 --> 33:07.942
♪

33:07.986 --> 33:09.117
- [moans softly]
- Great.

33:09.161 --> 33:11.467
I'm right here with you.

33:12.903 --> 33:14.993
- [moans]
- [exhales]

33:18.909 --> 33:22.000
[both breathing heavily]

33:23.131 --> 33:29.572
♪

33:34.577 --> 33:35.622
- So, did you have a good time?

33:35.665 --> 33:36.927
- First time on a movie set.

33:36.971 --> 33:39.060
It's not exactly
what I expected.

33:39.104 --> 33:41.671
- Yeah,
it's a little bit crazy.

33:41.715 --> 33:43.717
- Actually, I was thinking

33:43.760 --> 33:47.068
it kind of feels like a family.

33:47.112 --> 33:51.551
- Yeah, and families are
a little bit crazy.

33:52.813 --> 33:56.077
Um... listen,
you can come and visit anytime.

33:56.121 --> 33:57.165
- You sure?

33:57.209 --> 33:58.819
- Yeah, of course.

33:58.862 --> 34:00.690
Here. Come here.
- Thank you.

34:00.734 --> 34:02.301
Thank you.

34:05.130 --> 34:06.522
- Oh, whoa, Wes, whoa.

34:06.566 --> 34:07.915
That's not where
I was going with this.

34:07.958 --> 34:09.308
- Then maybe
you should change direction...

34:09.351 --> 34:10.786
- No, no, no, no.
You have to stop.

34:10.831 --> 34:13.790
This... it's not happening.
Ever.

34:13.833 --> 34:15.661
- [sighs]

34:15.705 --> 34:16.750
Oh, uh...

34:16.793 --> 34:18.534
- God.
- Okay, um...

34:18.578 --> 34:20.101
That was totally my fault.

34:20.145 --> 34:21.275
That was my mistake.
I...

34:21.320 --> 34:22.799
- No, no, no,
it's not a mistake.

34:22.842 --> 34:25.585
It's okay because it's...
You miss your mom

34:25.628 --> 34:28.891
and... and... it's confusing.

34:28.936 --> 34:30.677
And...

34:33.375 --> 34:35.072
There's no script for this.

34:35.116 --> 34:36.726
Gonna feel a lot
of different things,

34:36.770 --> 34:37.771
and none of them are wrong.

34:37.813 --> 34:40.947
- I feel angry, DeAnn.

34:40.991 --> 34:43.864
Like, she should have
just flown home.

34:45.170 --> 34:46.780
- Listen, Wes,

34:46.822 --> 34:50.262
even when you were going
through your rough patches,

34:50.304 --> 34:53.699
you were the center
of her world.

34:56.790 --> 34:59.009
- Unconditional love.

34:59.053 --> 35:00.010
Right?

35:00.054 --> 35:01.011
- Yeah.

35:01.055 --> 35:02.752
[both chuckle]

35:02.796 --> 35:05.103
- Mom was the definition.

35:07.017 --> 35:09.107
Okay, so...

35:11.370 --> 35:13.328
- Not a bad day at work, Clyde.

35:13.372 --> 35:16.723
- You too, Mr. Director, sir.

35:16.766 --> 35:18.290
- Sir...

35:23.164 --> 35:25.166
Today felt great.

35:25.210 --> 35:27.255
- The scene?

35:27.299 --> 35:29.127
Having you in my head like that
felt pretty...

35:29.170 --> 35:32.260
- No.
What I said before the scene.

35:32.304 --> 35:35.176
Sharing what I'm going through.

35:35.220 --> 35:38.397
You're right.
That's the way it should be.

35:44.446 --> 35:46.056
[drawer opens]

35:50.844 --> 35:54.152
[solemn music]

35:54.195 --> 35:55.718
What's this?

35:55.762 --> 35:56.937
- Read it.

35:56.980 --> 36:04.031
♪

36:10.429 --> 36:12.126
- Where'd you get this?

36:12.170 --> 36:14.172
- Terence gave it to me.

36:14.215 --> 36:17.305
After our sessions.

36:17.349 --> 36:19.786
He found him.

36:19.829 --> 36:21.222
My dad.

36:21.266 --> 36:23.311
Terence thinks that,

36:23.355 --> 36:24.791
based on our work together,

36:24.834 --> 36:27.185
it would be beneficial healing

36:27.228 --> 36:29.187
for me and for my narrative

36:29.230 --> 36:33.234
if I went to my dad
and met him

36:33.278 --> 36:36.803
and confronted him.

36:36.846 --> 36:38.979
And...
[sighs]

36:39.022 --> 36:41.329
I...
I thought a lot about it,

36:41.373 --> 36:45.115
and honestly... I don't know
what the right choice is.

36:45.159 --> 36:46.421
Maybe Terence is right.

36:46.465 --> 36:47.683
You know,
since he brought it up,

36:47.727 --> 36:49.729
not one pain in my stomach.

36:49.772 --> 36:51.731
- Terence is wrong.

36:51.774 --> 36:55.387
♪

36:55.430 --> 36:56.692
- You think so?

36:56.736 --> 36:58.303
- Yeah.

36:58.346 --> 37:00.957
Look, I am glad that
your stomach is feeling better.

37:01.001 --> 37:02.916
But Terence doesn't have
all the answers.

37:02.959 --> 37:04.874
Screw your dad.

37:04.918 --> 37:06.876
Screw the people who couldn't
be bothered to love us enough.

37:06.920 --> 37:08.878
We don't need them.

37:08.922 --> 37:10.315
We have each other.

37:10.358 --> 37:12.055
[Fink's "Cracks Appear"]

37:12.099 --> 37:16.103
- ♪ No need to cover up
fault lines ♪

37:16.146 --> 37:18.888
♪ They make us who we are

37:18.932 --> 37:21.108
♪ We are many

37:21.151 --> 37:25.417
♪ I've been trying
to hold it all together ♪

37:25.460 --> 37:27.897
♪ Throwing all my hope

37:27.941 --> 37:29.899
♪ My time my money

37:29.943 --> 37:32.250
♪

37:32.293 --> 37:34.513
♪ But nothing stops
the pressure ♪

37:34.556 --> 37:37.080
♪ From building up

37:37.124 --> 37:41.520
♪

37:41.563 --> 37:46.089
♪ And nothing stops
the gravity giving up ♪

37:46.133 --> 37:48.962
♪

37:49.005 --> 37:53.401
♪ Cracks appear
cracks appear ♪

37:53.445 --> 37:55.925
♪ From the inside out

37:55.969 --> 37:58.319
♪ Ooh...

37:58.363 --> 38:01.322
- Let's really try.

38:01.366 --> 38:02.889
- [exhales]

38:02.932 --> 38:05.021
I think we could create someone

38:05.065 --> 38:06.936
truly wonderful.

38:06.980 --> 38:08.938
♪ You could really
open me up... ♪

38:08.982 --> 38:10.331
- So do I.

38:10.375 --> 38:11.985
♪

38:12.028 --> 38:17.120
- ♪ Make 'em all disappear

38:17.164 --> 38:18.948
♪

38:18.992 --> 38:21.386
♪ Disappear

38:22.604 --> 38:24.214
- Hey.
[knocks]

38:24.258 --> 38:26.304
You have a minute?

38:27.479 --> 38:29.959
- Sure.
Come in.

38:30.003 --> 38:33.049
- I just wanted
to say thank you.

38:33.093 --> 38:35.138
The seminar the other day,

38:35.182 --> 38:38.228
I've been thinking about it
a lot.

38:38.272 --> 38:40.100
Are you okay?

38:40.143 --> 38:43.016
- I thought she'd cut ties
with this person.

38:44.104 --> 38:47.150
[tense music]

38:47.194 --> 38:51.807
♪

38:51.851 --> 38:52.895
- [sighs]

38:52.939 --> 38:55.333
Yeah, so did I.

38:55.376 --> 38:57.813
♪

38:57.857 --> 39:00.599
I swear,
I had no idea she was...

39:00.642 --> 39:05.081
♪

39:05.125 --> 39:06.213
- [sighs]

39:12.437 --> 39:14.830
- So, your official title
is "production assistant."

39:14.874 --> 39:16.484
And your unofficial title is

39:16.528 --> 39:18.573
"guy who gets everything
for anybody who asks."

39:18.617 --> 39:20.401
- Okay, I'm game.
Totally.

39:20.445 --> 39:22.577
- Great, so,
stay alert, be polite,

39:22.621 --> 39:24.579
and try and let the bullshit
roll off your back.

39:24.623 --> 39:26.407
- Got it, thank you.
This is amazing.

39:26.451 --> 39:27.582
- You're welcome.

39:27.626 --> 39:30.933
And don't kiss me again.

39:30.977 --> 39:33.632
- I'll do my best.

39:33.675 --> 39:35.460
- Good luck.
- Thanks.

39:35.503 --> 39:37.375
[chuckles]

39:37.418 --> 39:38.854
- [laughs]
- Yeah, the kid was, like,

39:38.898 --> 39:40.465
nine years old.
He looks at me, dead serious,

39:40.508 --> 39:42.031
and he's like, "Step aside."

39:42.075 --> 39:43.816
Young blood's gonna show you
how it's done."

39:43.859 --> 39:45.426
- [laughs]
- And then

39:45.470 --> 39:47.080
he plays "Chopsticks."

39:47.123 --> 39:48.081
- [laughing]
What?

39:48.124 --> 39:50.910
- [laughing]
Yeah.

39:50.953 --> 39:53.086
- What?
[laughs]

39:53.129 --> 39:54.522
- That laugh.

39:54.566 --> 39:55.784
I think I need to bottle it.

39:55.828 --> 39:57.395
- [laughs]

39:59.614 --> 40:01.355
- I need a minute with her,
please.

40:01.399 --> 40:03.531
- Yeah.

40:03.575 --> 40:04.793
- What's up?

40:04.837 --> 40:06.795
- I told you
not to mess with Hope,

40:06.839 --> 40:07.883
and you ignored me.

40:07.927 --> 40:09.929
Congratulations.
- Shit.

40:09.972 --> 40:11.713
- And now Terence is wondering

40:11.757 --> 40:13.454
why you're on
"Reel Deal Hollywood"

40:13.498 --> 40:14.803
with a woman
who is a pariah at IHM.

40:14.847 --> 40:16.849
- Terence saw this?
- Terence showed me.

40:16.892 --> 40:18.764
- Shit.
Okay, wait, wait.

40:18.807 --> 40:20.635
I could come up with a reason
that I had to see her.

40:20.679 --> 40:22.115
This is just a minor issue.

40:22.158 --> 40:24.073
- It's not minor to me.

40:24.117 --> 40:26.075
He's my boss.
I have to work with him

40:26.119 --> 40:27.468
every day,

40:27.512 --> 40:29.339
putting my ass on the line
for you,

40:29.383 --> 40:30.515
my career...

40:30.558 --> 40:32.038
- I have a lot
on the line here, too.

40:32.081 --> 40:34.475
- I could be fired,
even disbarred,

40:34.519 --> 40:35.824
for what I'm doing.

40:35.868 --> 40:37.086
- Do you not want to help me?

40:37.130 --> 40:38.523
- Help you what?

40:38.566 --> 40:40.829
What's even the plan here,
Megan?

40:40.873 --> 40:43.832
Go to the police?
The press?

40:43.876 --> 40:45.834
What's your next move?

40:45.878 --> 40:48.881
- Why are you grilling me
like this, Shaun?

40:48.924 --> 40:50.491
I thought you were on my side.

40:50.535 --> 40:51.710
- No, I am.

40:51.753 --> 40:53.625
I just...

40:53.668 --> 40:55.017
[sighs]

40:55.061 --> 40:58.020
I think I need
to take a step back.

40:58.064 --> 41:00.022
- Wow.

41:00.066 --> 41:02.024
[tense music]

41:02.068 --> 41:04.636
So, you're choosing IHM?

41:04.679 --> 41:05.811
Terence?

41:05.854 --> 41:07.508
- No.

41:07.552 --> 41:09.815
I'm choosing me.

41:09.858 --> 41:16.909
♪

41:28.094 --> 41:35.144
♪

41:37.059 --> 41:38.191
- Hey...

41:38.234 --> 41:39.540
I know we're about to shoot.

41:39.584 --> 41:42.674
I just need a moment to just...

41:44.502 --> 41:45.503
Zach...
- I'm sorry.

41:45.546 --> 41:46.765
We need to be careful.

41:46.808 --> 41:49.463
They're listening to us.

41:49.507 --> 41:53.075
Terence is always listening.

41:53.119 --> 41:55.817
- What are you...
- I saw the photos

41:55.861 --> 41:57.427
of you and Hope.

41:57.471 --> 41:58.907
I saw them, Megan.
I saw them,

41:58.951 --> 42:00.866
and I realized it was you.

42:00.909 --> 42:03.564
I'm the person you were
supposed to meet yesterday.

42:03.608 --> 42:06.915
I'm That's boyfriend.

42:06.959 --> 42:08.569
You want dirt on IHM?

42:08.613 --> 42:10.440
Well, I've got it.

42:10.484 --> 42:13.139
Megan, I've got stories that'll
make your blood run cold.

42:13.182 --> 42:18.057
♪

42:18.100 --> 42:20.799
- I have no idea
what you're talking about.

42:20.842 --> 42:22.931
♪

42:24.193 --> 42:27.153
[rock music]

42:27.196 --> 42:34.508
♪

42:42.647 --> 42:45.606
[dramatic music]

42:45.650 --> 42:52.744
♪

